*[[Broadcom]] [https://www.broadcom.com/products/wireless/wireless-lan-bluetooth/bcm4389 BCM4389] • Wi-Fi 6E, 2T2R (TBS) :Frequency Range: 6025.0 - 6985.0 MHz <!-- Wi-Fi 6E and Bluetooth 5 Combo Chipset with 6GHz/160MHz support
The BCM4389 is a low-power, highly integrated Wi-Fi 6E and Bluetooth 5 combo chip optimized for mobile handset :applications where high performance, low power consumption and small solution size are key requirements. The device includes support for 160MHz wide channels, 6GHz band support, Tri-band Simultaneous (TBS) :Wi-Fi capability and BT Xstream Dual Bluetooth capability. The chip includes a power management unit that simplifies the system power topology and allows :for direct operation from a mobile platform battery while maximizing battery life. *Features :Full Wi-Fi 6E support with legacy compatibility :Tri-Band Simultaneous Wi-Fi, WPA3+ security :6GHz band support, 160MHz channel width :BT Xstream Dual Bluetooth capability *Applications: :Low-power mobile devices, AR/VR devices --> ==See also== *[[Broadcom BCM94378 FCPAGBE]] *[[Broadcom BCM94389 FCPAGBE]] *[[Broadcom BCM94398 FCREF7X7]]
